      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["# Fish Audio S2 integration\n\nThis workflow demonstrates both normal TTS Text and SRT generation with Fish Audio S2 Pro. The default example is the pigeon-parliament dialogue below.\n\n- `[Character]` is the suite's public character-switching syntax.\n- Speaker 1 is always the connected `opt_narrator`; Speaker 2-5 are positional Fish references.\n- Native Multi-Speaker keeps all turns in one Fish request. Custom Character Switching generates each parsed segment independently.\n- Every connected voice must have an exact reference transcript. Character Voices loads `.reference.txt` automatically when available.\n\nDocs: [Character Switching Guide](https://github.com/diodiogod/TTS-Audio-Suite/blob/main/docs/CHARACTER_SWITCHING_GUIDE.md) | [Tag Editor Guide](https://github.com/diodiogod/TTS-Audio-Suite/blob/main/docs/MULTILINE_TTS_TAG_EDITOR_GUIDE.md) | [Official Fish Speech](https://github.com/fishaudio/fish-speech)"]
    },
