    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [650, 620],
      "size": [900, 260],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 13,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["# Fish inline instructions\n\nThe suite keeps its public inline-tag syntax as `<instruction>`, for example:\n\n`[Alice] Hello <excited> everyone.`\n\nAt the Fish adapter boundary, supported Fish instructions are converted to Fish's native `[instruction]` syntax. Character tags remain suite tags and are never blindly converted. Fish has no separate language parameter; with `Auto Inline Tag`, mapped alias languages become natural-language instructions such as `<French>`. Set `language_prompting` to `Off` when the text should control language alone.\n\nSee the [Fish S2 model card](https://huggingface.co/fishaudio/s2-pro) for official prompting examples."]
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [650, 1120],
      "size": [900, 250],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 14,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": ["# Performance and model options\n\n- `compile=True` is recommended after the first slower compilation run.\n- `quantization=bnb_nf4` can substantially reduce VRAM, while `bnb_int8` is generally slower.\n- The model dropdown lists local checkpoints first when available, followed by downloadable options.\n- Fish native duration targeting is not exposed here because it is not a Fish S2 feature; SRT timing is handled by the suite's standard timing engine.\n\nThe first text and SRT branches are ready to run independently. Preview the branch you want to test."]
    }
